reviewText: I am a huge royal follower and HM Queen Elizabeth II is one of my all time favorties to learn and study about. this Doc is beautifully done and has some stunning footage. It has a very regal feel when you watch the footage and listen to the music it is played too. I highly recommend this wonderful DVD for anyone who has a love for Royalty.
One of kind DVD with historical footage. I am so happy to have bought this. Thank you.

Very good review of the Queen's life and reign.
Again, this DVD was given as a gift and I was never informed whether it was good or not.
Well what can I say I love Queen Elizabeth she has & is doing her Job very well. I believe she is loved by many close and afar.
It is a very good depiction of the Queen's life. I highly recommend  it  to anyone who is interested in royalty.

Over the last 20 years or so, I have become a great admirer of the queen of England.  Even though I am an American, I have the utmost respect and admiration for a woman who dedicated her life to the royal service how ever long or short it may when she was only 18 years old.  Many of the people who have been interviewed on some of the DVD's I have about the Queen have said that she is the glue that holds the country together.  This DVD helped me to understand hermore as a person and not just the Queen.

As a monarchist, I'm always interested in books about royalty and although there's always the temptation to think that it would be nice to be part of such a fairy-tale world, the reality is really quite different and more like hard work than days of fun.

Even if you're not a monarchist or a fan of Britain's royal family you should watch this just in order to see what duty and self-sacrifice really means. When she was 16 she made a tremendous discovery: for whatever reason a visit from the monarch MEANS something to people, it's something they'll remember for the rest of their lives, so YOU MUST NEVER LET PEOPLE DOWN! Her beloved father, George VI, taught her that, and she has lived by it ever since.

This dvd was not worth what I paid for it. There's little information that isn't already known by most. You would do much better by buying a good biography of HM Elizabeth II. The whole thing seemed cheap, from the quality of the video footage and audio to the over-used news footage that everyone has seen 100 times.
